{"parse":{"title":"however","pageid":4794,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|however}}, {{m|enm|how-ever}}, {{m|enm|how-evere}}; equivalent to {{univ|en|how|ever|notext=1}}. Compare {{m|en|howsoever}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/haʊˈɛvə/|a=RP}}\n* {{enPR|houĕvʹər|a=GA,CA}}, {{IPA|en|/haʊˈɛvɚ/}}\n** {{audio|en|en-us-however.ogg|a=California}}\n* {{IPA|en|/hɑˈwɛvə(ɹ)/|a=NYC}}\n* {{IPA|en|/hæɔˈevə/|a=AU}}\n* {{IPA|en|/hæʊˈevə/|a=NZ}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɛvə(ɹ)|s=3}}\n* {{hyphenation|en|how|ev|er}}\n\n===Adverb===\n{{en-adv|-}}\n\n# {{lb|en|conjunctive}} {{U|nevertheless}}; [[yet]], [[still]]; [[in spite of]] that.\n#: {{syn|en|nonetheless|notwithstanding|that said|still and all|in any case|after all|anyway|Thesaurus:nevertheless|Thesaurus:regardless}}\n#: {{cot|en|but<qq:conjunction>}}<!--different POS but same meaning-->\n#: {{ux|en|He told me not to do it. '''However''', I did it anyway. / I did it anyway, '''however'''. / I, '''however''', did it anyway.}}\n#: {{ux|en|She wanted to go; '''however''', she decided against it.}}\n#: {{ux|en|I didn't argue with him; I still think, '''however''', that he is wrong.}}\n#* {{RQ:Besant Ivory Gate|chapter=Prologue|passage=Thus, when he drew up instructions in lawyer language, he expressed the important words by an initial, a medial, or a final consonant, and made scratches for all the words between; his clerks, '''however''', understood him very well.}}\n#* {{RQ:Maxwell Mirror and the Lamp|chapter=2|passage=''That'' the young Mr. Churchills liked—but they did not like him coming round of an evening and drinking weak whisky-and-water while he held forth on railway debentures and corporation loans. Mr. Barrett, '''however''', by fawning and flattery, seemed to be able to make not only Mrs. Churchill but everyone else do what he desired.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2013-06-29|volume=407|issue=8842|page=72–3|magazine=w:The Economist\n|title=[http://www.economist.com/news/international/science-and-technology/21580133-how-microbes-promote-liver-cancer-overweight-punch-gut A punch in the gut]\n|passage=Mostly, the microbiome is beneficial. It helps with digestion and enables people to extract a lot more calories from their food than would otherwise be possible. Research over the past few years, '''however''', has implicated it in diseases from atherosclerosis to asthma to autism.}}\n# {{lb|en|conjunctive}} In [[contrast]].\n#: {{ux|en|The conference itself went very well. The party afterwards, '''however''', was a disaster.}}\n# {{lb|en|degree|fused relative}} {{U|regardless of}} [[how]]; [[no matter]] [[how]]\n#: {{syn|en|howsoever|howso|howsoevermuch}}\n#: {{ux|en|'''However''' clear you think you've been, and '''however''' many questions you [[may've]] answered, there'll always remain some doubts.}}\n#: {{ux|en|Any rule of thumb, '''however''' true (it is), is useless unless you understand its underlying logic.}}\n#: {{ux|en|'''However''' much I study, I never get good grades.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1811|author=[[s:Author:Jane Austen|Jane Austen]]|title=s:Sense and Sensibility|section=[[s:Sense and Sensibility/Chapter 42|Chapter 42]]|passage=Elinor, '''however''' little concerned in it, joined in their discourse; and Marianne, who had the knack of finding her way in every house to the library, however it might be avoided by the family in general, soon procured herself a book.}}\n# {{lb|en|manner|fused relative}} {{U|regardless of}} [[how]]; [[regardless of]] the way in which.\n#: {{syn|en|howsoever|howso|anyhow}}\n#: {{ux|en|Let me know when you've had your interview, '''however''' it goes.}}\n#: {{ux|en|'''However''' we do this, it isn't going to work.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1811|author=[[s:Author:Jane Austen|Jane Austen]]|title=s:Sense and Sensibility|section=[[s:Sense and Sensibility/Chapter 42|Chapter 42]]|passage=Elinor, however little concerned in it, joined in their discourse; and Marianne, who had the knack of finding her way in every house to the library, '''however''' it might be avoided by the family in general, soon procured herself a book.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2013-06-21|author=w:Oliver Burkeman\n|volume=189|issue=2|page=48|magazine=w:The Guardian Weekly\n|title=[http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2013/may/10/conscious-computing-twitter-facebook-google The tao of tech]\n|passage=But the real way to build a successful online business is to be better than your rivals at undermining people's control of their own attention. Partly, this is a result of how online advertising has traditionally worked: advertisers pay for clicks, and a click is a click, '''however''' it's obtained.}}\n# {{lb|en|manner|fused relative}} In any [[way]] in which; [[how]].\n#: {{ux|en|She offered to help '''however''' she could.}}\n#: {{ux|en|Wear your hair '''however''' you want.}}\n# {{lb|en|informal|manner}} In any way that one likes or chooses; in a haphazard or spontaneous way.\n#: {{ux|en|I don't care; just do it '''however'''.}}\n#: {{ux|en|Nothing was really planned; things just happened '''however'''.}}\n# {{senseid|en|interrogative}} {{lb|en|interrogative}} [[how|How]] [[ever]]: {{non-gloss|an emphatic form of '''''[[how]]''''', used to ask in what manner}}.\n#: {{syn|en|[[how]] + [[the dickens]]|Thesaurus:the dickens}}\n#: {{cot|en|whatever<id:interrogative>}}\n#: {{ux|en|I thought it was impossible. '''However''' were you able to do it?}}\n# {{lb|en|obsolete}} [[in any case|In any case]], [[at any rate]], [[at all events]].\n#* {{circa|1680}}, John Tillotson:\n#*: Our chief end and highest interest is happiness : And this is happiness to be freed from all (if it may) [or] '''however''' from the greatest evils.\n\n====Usage notes====\nTraditionally, some commentators have objected to the use of \"however\" at the start of a sentence in the sense of \"nevertheless\", but in practice this is widely accepted if followed immediately by a comma. The choice of position depends on the word being emphasized, which is usually the one immediately before.\n\nThe use of a comma before \"however\" as a means of connecting independent clauses in the sense of \"nevertheless\", as in \"She wanted to go, '''however''' she decided against it\", is traditionally considered an error, equivalent to using \"however\" as a proscribed conjunction (see below). Compare the prescriptively correct sentence \"She wanted to go, <u>but</u> she decided against it\", which uses a true conjunction \"but\". Similarly, mispunctuating it between commas makes for an ambiguous modifier because '''however''' could go with either clause.\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|en|however one slices it}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top-see|nevertheless|nevertheless|that being said}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|megjithatë}}\n* Arabic: {{t+|ar|لٰكِن}}, {{t+|ar|لٰكِنَّ}}, {{t|ar|وَلٰكِن|tr=wa-lākin}}, {{t|ar|وَلٰكِنَّ|tr=wa-lākinna}}, {{t|ar|رَغْمَ ذٰلِك}}\n*: Moroccan Arabic: {{t|ary|وخى هد شي|tr=waḵa had ši}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|սակայն}}\n* Asturian: {{t|ast|sin embargu}}\n* Basque: {{t+|eu|haatik}}\n* Belarusian: {{t+|be|адна́к}}, {{t|be|тым не ме́нш}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|оба́че}}\n* Burmese: {{t+|my|ဒါပေမဲ့}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|tanmateix}}, {{t+|ca|nogensmenys}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|但是|tr=dànshì}}, {{t+|cmn|可是|tr=kěshì}}, {{t+|cmn|不過|tr=búguò}}, {{t+|cmn|卻|tr=què}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|nicméně}}, {{t+|cs|však}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|dog}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|daarentegen}}, {{t+|nl|echter}}, {{t+|nl|evenwel}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|kontraŭe}}, {{t+|eo|tamen}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|kuitenkin}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|cependant}}, {{t+|fr|pourtant}}, {{t+|fr|néanmoins}}, {{t+|fr|toutefois}}, {{t+|fr|nonobstant}}\n*: Old French: {{t|fro|nepourquant}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|მიუხედავად ამისა}}\n* German: {{t+|de|jedoch}}, {{t+|de|allerdings}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|όμως}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|μέντοι}}\n* Hebrew: {{t|he|אף על פי כן}}, {{t|he|למרות זאת}}\n* Hindi: {{t|hi|फिर भी}}, {{t+|hi|यद्यपि}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|mégis}}, {{t+|hu|viszont}}, {{t+|hu|azonban}}, {{t+|hu|mindazonáltal}}\n* Ilocano: {{t|ilo|ngem}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|áfach}}\n*: Old Irish: {{t|sga|immurgu}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|però}}, {{t+|it|nonostante}}, {{t+|it|tuttavia}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|しかし|tr=shikashi}}, {{t+|ja|が|tr=ga}}, {{t+|ja|でも|tr=demo}}, {{t+|ja|けれども|tr=keredomo}}, {{t+|ja|けれど|tr=keredo}}, {{t|ja|けども|tr=kedomo}}, {{t+|ja|けど|tr=kedo}}\n* Kapampangan: {{t|pam|onyang}} {{qualifier|formally}}, {{t|pam|oneng}} {{qualifier|colloquially}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|그러나}}, {{t+|ko|하지만}}, {{t+|ko|나|alt=-(으)나}}, {{t+|ko|지만|alt=-지만}}, {{t+|ko|만|alt=-만}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{t+|kmr|her wiha}}, {{t+|kmr|dîsa jî}}, {{t+|kmr|lê}}\n* Latin: {{t+|la|tamen}}, {{t|la|utut}}\n* Lingala: {{t|ln|ndé}}\n* Lushootseed: {{t|lut|ʔiwəɬ}}\n* Luxembourgish: {{t+|lb|awer}}, {{t+|lb|awer}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|меѓутоа}}\n* Malay: {{t|ms|walau bagaimana}}\n* Maltese: {{t|mt|madankollu}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t+|nb|ikke desto mindre}}, {{t+|nb|imidlertid}}, {{t+|nb|men}}\n* Occitan: {{t+|oc|pasmens}}\n* Pannonian Rusyn: {{t|rsk|заш лєм}}, {{t|rsk|медзитим}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|اما|tr=ammâ}}, {{t|fa|با این حال}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|jednakże}}, {{t+|pl|jednak}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|no entanto}}, {{t+|pt|entretanto}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|totuși}}, {{t+|ro|însă}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|одна́ко}}, {{t+|ru|тем не ме́нее}}\n* Scots: {{t|sco|houaniver}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|ge-tà}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|међутим}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|međutim}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|však}}\n* Slovene: {{t|sl|vendar}}\n* Sorbian:\n*: Lower Sorbian: {{t|dsb|pak}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|sin embargo}}, {{t+|es|no obstante}}, {{t+|es|mas}}, {{t+|es|empero}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|däremot}}, {{t+|sv|dock}}, {{t+|sv|emellertid}}\n* Tagalog: {{t|tl|subalit}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|อย่างไรก็ตาม|tr=yàang rai gôr dtaam}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|bununla birlikte}}, {{t+|tr|ancak}}, {{t+|tr|lakin}}, {{t+|tr|fakat}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|одна́к}}, {{t|uk|проте́}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|biroq}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|tuy nhiên}}\n* Votic: {{t|vot|sorovnoo}}\n* Walloon: {{t+|wa|portant}}, {{t+|wa|mins nerén}}, {{t|wa|mågré tot}}\n* West Flemish: {{t|vls|pertank}}\n* Zazaki: {{t+|zza|labelê}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|to whatever extent or degree}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|все пак}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|kiom ajn}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|[[kuinka]] [[tahansa]]}}, {{t|fi|[[miten]] [[tahansa]]}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|peu importe}}\n* German: {{t|de|[[egal]] [[wie]]}}\n* Hungarian: {{gloss|with verbs or predicate adjectives}} {{t+|hu|bármennyire}} / {{t+|hu|akármennyire}}, {{gloss|with predicate adjectives only}} {{t+|hu|bármilyen}} / {{t+|hu|akármilyen}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|dá}} {{qualifier|followed by abstract noun}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|сепак}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t|nb|uansett hvor}}, {{t|nb|uten omsyn til hvor}}\n* Spanish: {{t|es|comoquiera}}, {{t|es|comoquier}}, {{t+|es|como sea}}, {{t|es|[[cuantoquiera]] [[que]]}} {{q|however much|rare}}, {{t|es|[[cuanto]] [[sea]]}} {{q|however much}}, {{t|es|así como así}}\n* Welsh: {{t|cy|er mor}}, {{t|cy|pa mor}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|no matter how}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|por más que}}, {{t|es|[[aunque]] más}}, {{t|es|[[por]] [[muy]]}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|in any way in which}}\n* Spanish: {{t|es|[[comoquiera]] que}}, {{t|es|[[como sea]] [[que]]}} {{q|present}}, {{t|es|[[como]] [[fuere]] [[que]]}} {{q|future}}, {{t|es|[[como]] [[fuese]] [[que]]}} {{q|past}}, {{t|es|[[como]] [[fuera]] [[que]]}} {{q|past}}, {{t|es|[[de cualquier manera]] [[que]]}}, {{t|es|[[de cualquier modo]] [[que]]}}, {{t|es|[[de cualquier manera]] [[que]]}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top-see|in any way that one likes or chooses|anyway}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|mal que bien}}, {{t|es|bien que mal}}, {{t|es|comoquiera}}, {{t|es|comoquier}}, {{t|es|de cualquier modo}}, {{t|es|de cualquier forma}}, {{t|es|de cualquier manera}}, {{t+|es|como sea}} {{q|present}}, {{t|es|[[como]] [[fuese]]}} {{q|past}}, {{t|es|[[como]] [[fuera]]}} {{q|past}}, {{t|es|[[como]] [[fuere]]}} {{q|future}}, {{t|es|[[así]] que asá}}, {{t|es|[[así]] que asado}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|jakkoli}}\n* Dutch: {{t|nl|eender hoe}}\n* Finnish: {{t|fi|[[miten]] [[tahansa]]}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|akármennyire}} ({{t+|hu|is}}), {{t+|hu|bármennyire}} ({{t+|hu|is}})\n* Indonesian: {{t+check|id|tapi}}, {{t+check|id|tetapi}}, {{t+check|id|namun}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|arae}}\n* Norwegian: {{t|no|på den måten}}, {{t|no|på hvilken måte}}; {{t|no|uansett hvor}}, {{t|no|hvor mye}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|oricum}}; {{t|ro|oricât de}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|hur som helst}}\n* Volapük: {{t+|vo|ye}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}} <!-- correspond either to \"no matter how\" or \"in any way in which\", which was originally listed as one sense, \"in whatever way or manner\" -->\n* Arabic: {{t|ar|كَيْفَ}}, {{t|ar|كَيْفَمَا}}\n* Dutch: {{t|nl|hoe dan ook}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|kiel ajn}}\n* French: {{t|fr|de quelque manière que ce soit}}, {{t|fr|quelle que soit sa manière}}\n* German: {{t|de|wie auch immer}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|akárhogy}} ({{t+|hu|is}}), {{t+|hu|akárhogyan}} ({{t+|hu|is}}), {{t+|hu|bárhogy}} ({{t+|hu|is}}), {{t+|hu|bárhogyan}} ({{t+|hu|is}}), {{t|hu|ahogy csak}}, {{t|hu|ahogyan csak}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|comunque}}\n* Portuguese: {{t|pt|de qualquer modo}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Conjunction===\n{{en-head|conj}}\n\n# {{lb|en|proscribed}} {{U|but}}, [[yet]], [[though]], [[although]].\n#: {{ux|en|*She wanted to go, '''however''' she decided against it.|q=proscribed}}\n\n====Usage notes====\nSee the usage notes for adverb senses, above.\n\n===References===\n* {{R:Webster 1913|however}}\n* {{R:Dictionary.com|however}}\n* \"[https://web.archive.org/web/20071208172827/http://dictionary.cambridge.org/define.asp?key=38295&dict=CALD however (degree)]\" in Cambridge Advanced Learner's Dictionary (Cambridge University Press, 2007)\n* \"[https://web.archive.org/web/20071208172837/http://dictionary.cambridge.org/define.asp?key=38298&dict=CALD however (despite)]\" in Cambridge Advanced Learner's Dictionary (Cambridge University Press, 2007)\n* \"[https://web.archive.org/web/20071208172832/http://dictionary.cambridge.org/define.asp?key=38296&dict=CALD however (way)]\" in Cambridge Advanced Learner's Dictionary (Cambridge University Press, 2007)\n* {{R:Lexico|however}}\n* ''Oxford English Dictionary'', second edition (1989)\n* ''Random House Webster's Unabridged Electronic Dictionary'' (1987-1996)\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=eehorvw|everwho|whoever}}\n\n{{cln|en|conjunctive adverbs|degree adverbs|intensifiers}}"}}